# Job carousel scroll animation — hands off

**Never change the job cards scroll/scale animation unless the user explicitly asks to change it.**

This includes indirect changes while fixing layout, nav alignment, chips, or other UI work.

## Protected files

- `components/job-carousel.tsx` — scroll listener, scale math, transform styles, transform origin
- `standalone/focus-scroll/` — if re-integrated
- `app/globals.css` — only the focus-scroll / carousel animation utilities, if present

## Do not change without explicit request

- `MIN_SCALE`, `MOBILE_BREAKPOINT`, `range`, scale interpolation
- `transform`, `transform-origin`, `will-change` on card wrappers
- `window.innerWidth` vs `container.clientWidth` mobile detection
- Switching between React state scales vs direct DOM updates (FocusScroll)
- Scroll snap, padding-block, or opacity/saturate tied to scroll focus

## Allowed without asking

- Category chips, empty states, filtering, copy
- Adding props that do not affect scroll/scale behavior
- Import/path refactors that leave animation logic identical

## When layout work might affect cards

Fix alignment via page shell, nav, or shared layout classes — **not** by changing transform origin, scale logic, or card wrapper animation classes.

If animation and layout truly conflict, stop and ask the user instead of changing animation code.
